title: boop: solana-instruction missing feature-flag
boop: added missing feature flags
Move crates dependencies to workspace dependencies + unpinning
body:
The goal of moving deps at the workspace level it forces all crates the same lib version if needed.
In otherwords when you upgrade a lib, it forces software dev to migrated all crates too and not forgetting about any one of them, which is typically a desirable outcome.

As for Unpinning crates (using caret ^), this will allow other user of your crates to apply patches to common libraries they share with you. When we pin like "solana-pubkey = 2.2.1" we cannot benefits from say anza publishing bugfix/security fix of 2.2.3, etc.

Finally I added `protobuf-src` to various parser that needs to compile proto files as it offers better portability across development environment.

title: [Bugfix] - Fix build when adding `yellowstone-vixen` as a dependency through Github link
body:
When `yellowstone-vixen` is added as a crate/workspace dependency using its Github link, its `topograph` dependency fails to build, due to having a non-existent branch specified as the source.

The fix is to simply specify the exact revision the `0.4.0` version of `topograph` that was present in `Cargo.lock`.

An alternative solution would be to simply specify the released [`0.4.0` version on crates.io](https://crates.io/crates/topograph).

I aimed to make as little of a change as possible, but if you'd like to see this change, I'd be happy to test it out.
